		<IUseCase type="e">
			<_id type="a">GUID e01b22a0-b686-445f-9a63-352baedcfdf6</_id>
			<_myState type="a">8192</_myState>
			<_name type="a">Movement</_name>
			<_modifiedTimeWeak type="a">6.2.2026::10:35:39</_modifiedTimeWeak>
			<_description type="p"><IDescription type="e">
				<_text type="a">The transition to the gate movement in the given direction requires the following steps:%0D
1. Turn on the collision detector%0D
2. Optional activation of the signal lamp%0D
3. Turning on the gate drive%0D
During the movement taking place in a given direction, the following actions should be repeated every fixed period of time:%0D
1. Send a signal about the last travelled distance to the Controller%0D
2. Check the occurance of a collision and if the collision detector signals it, stop the gate movement.%0D
3. If the signaling option is active, flash the lamp</_text>
			</IDescription>
			</_description>
			<_modifiedTime type="a">6.2.2026::16:46:46</_modifiedTime>
			<_lastID type="a">2</_lastID>
			<weakCGTime type="a">6.2.2026::10:35:39</weakCGTime>
			<strongCGTime type="a">1.2.1990::0:0:0</strongCGTime>
